cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and neural machine translation (NMT). The use of LMBR n-gram posteriors and batched beam decoding are common techniques in NMT research, which are typically published in cs.CL. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as NMT is a subfield of machine learning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as NMT is a type of AI application. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are less likely as they are not directly related to NLP or NMT.
